WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.880 --> 00:00:03.670
One touch!

2
00:00:04.960 --> 00:00:05.980
One touch!

3
00:00:05.980 --> 00:00:08.000
He sure is persistent...

4
00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:09.730
That brat with the glasses.

5
00:00:09.980 --> 00:00:12.110
Would you let me set the timing

6
00:00:12.520 --> 00:00:14.500
for the three-person block?

7
00:00:19.580 --> 00:00:21.620
They finally got a clean one in.

8
00:00:22.120 --> 00:00:23.670
Total defense.

9
00:00:44.310 --> 00:00:50.980
Karasuno High School vs Shiratorizawa Academy

10
00:00:44.310 --> 00:00:50.980
Haikyu!!

11
00:01:55.010 --> 00:01:58.970
Karasuno              Shiratorizawa

12
00:01:56.310 --> 00:01:58.410
All right!

13
00:01:58.970 --> 00:02:01.770
Nishinoya, nice receive!

14
00:01:59.470 --> 00:02:03.930
Episode 04: The Halo Around the Moon

15
00:02:01.770 --> 00:02:04.430
It was only possible because 
you all narrowed the gap.

16
00:02:06.980 --> 00:02:08.680
Great job on the block timing!

17
00:02:08.680 --> 00:02:10.150
Oh, right.

18
00:02:11.350 --> 00:02:12.570
I see!

19
00:02:13.110 --> 00:02:16.480
So that block really wasn't 
done to stop Ushiwaka,

20
00:02:16.480 --> 00:02:19.550
but to guide where the ball was going to go.

21
00:02:19.550 --> 00:02:21.370
Nice combo play!

22
00:02:21.760 --> 00:02:23.960
That was sort of like mobbing.

23
00:02:24.520 --> 00:02:25.830
Mobbing?

24
00:02:26.480 --> 00:02:31.290
Um... Mobbing is where smaller 
birds will attack larger,

25
00:02:31.290 --> 00:02:35.340
predatory birds in groups 
to try to chase them away.

26
00:02:37.220 --> 00:02:40.090
You know some pretty cool words, Yacchan.

27
00:02:42.490 --> 00:02:44.730
Using a connecting block as a starting point,

28
00:02:44.730 --> 00:02:47.030
they were able to connect everything 
naturally in that volley.

29
00:02:47.960 --> 00:02:50.120
They were finally able to give it shape.

30
00:02:50.120 --> 00:02:51.190
Yeah.

31
00:02:51.530 --> 00:02:55.050
Total defense! So cool!

32
00:02:55.510 --> 00:02:57.110
Even if we can't stop him by blocking,

33
00:02:57.960 --> 00:03:00.570
we'll be able to fight Ushiwaka with this.

34
00:03:05.040 --> 00:03:08.330
They were finally able to lift up
 one of Ushiwaka's spikes.

35
00:03:08.330 --> 00:03:10.440
Things are getting interesting.

36
00:03:10.440 --> 00:03:14.580
it. They wasted two sets.

37
00:03:14.580 --> 00:03:16.760
Is that old guy a tsundere?

38
00:03:16.760 --> 00:03:18.510
That was uncalled for.

39
00:03:19.010 --> 00:03:20.820
Asahi, nice serve!

40
00:03:26.120 --> 00:03:26.950
Out!

41
00:03:29.800 --> 00:03:31.520
All right!

42
00:03:31.830 --> 00:03:33.270
Seriously?

43
00:03:34.650 --> 00:03:36.880
All right, they broke through!

44
00:03:36.880 --> 00:03:38.860
Take this set!

45
00:03:39.730 --> 00:03:42.290
They definitely got us with 
that serve, but we're going to

46
00:03:42.290 --> 00:03:43.840
hurry up and turn things back around!

47
00:03:43.840 --> 00:03:44.760
Right!

48
00:03:45.320 --> 00:03:47.910
Be Courageous Warriors
Shiratorizawa Academy Volleyball Club

49
00:03:45.320 --> 00:03:48.010
Asahi, one more! Nice serve!

50
00:03:49.540 --> 00:03:50.030
Tsutomu!

51
00:03:50.030 --> 00:03:50.600
Right!

52
00:03:51.000 --> 00:03:52.470
Nice receive!

53
00:03:52.470 --> 00:03:53.420
Ohira-san.

54
00:03:53.420 --> 00:03:53.960
Got it!

55
00:03:54.280 --> 00:03:55.760
It wasn't Ushiwaka this time?

56
00:03:55.760 --> 00:03:59.060
I'm sure they'd worry about his 
stamina if it was every time.

57
00:03:59.510 --> 00:04:00.880
Ready, and...

58
00:04:06.550 --> 00:04:07.510
Tch.

59
00:04:07.510 --> 00:04:08.470
Feint!

60
00:04:10.200 --> 00:04:11.930
Sorry! It's going—

61
00:04:14.060 --> 00:04:16.770
Victory!

62
00:04:15.000 --> 00:04:16.770
Yeah!

63
00:04:16.770 --> 00:04:20.730
Shiratorizawa           Karasuno

64
00:04:17.120 --> 00:04:19.340
Not yet. We still need two points.

65
00:04:19.340 --> 00:04:20.730
Just how righteous are you?

66
00:04:21.310 --> 00:04:24.160
This puts Ushiwaka on the back line...

67
00:04:24.160 --> 00:04:25.030
But...

68
00:04:25.760 --> 00:04:27.780
that means he gets to serve.

69
00:04:35.830 --> 00:04:36.660
It's mine!

70
00:04:38.050 --> 00:04:38.970
Get the last one over!

71
00:04:38.970 --> 00:04:39.820
Ryu!

72
00:04:38.970 --> 00:04:40.250
Got it!

73
00:04:41.640 --> 00:04:42.920
Chance ball!

74
00:04:46.790 --> 00:04:48.260
Gimme!

75
00:04:52.520 --> 00:04:53.230
Where is he—

76
00:04:55.730 --> 00:04:56.650
A dump?!

77
00:04:57.040 --> 00:04:58.610
!

78
00:05:04.280 --> 00:05:07.280
Be Courageous Warriors

79
00:05:04.280 --> 00:05:07.980
Nice kill, Shirabu!

80
00:05:08.670 --> 00:05:11.440
Shirabu! Shirabu!

81
00:05:10.050 --> 00:05:12.450
Depending on Ushijima-san

82
00:05:14.440 --> 00:05:15.980
isn't my only job.

83
00:05:16.700 --> 00:05:17.740
All right!

84
00:05:17.740 --> 00:05:19.030
Not bad...

85
00:05:17.940 --> 00:05:19.420
Nice job, Shirabu!

86
00:05:19.420 --> 00:05:21.880
Karasuno             Shiratorizawa

87
00:05:22.450 --> 00:05:25.960
Sorry. It would have been 
better if I hadn't touched it.

88
00:05:25.960 --> 00:05:28.640
Nah, I wouldn't have been 
able to get that either way.

89
00:05:29.400 --> 00:05:31.800
This isn't where we relax!

90
00:05:31.800 --> 00:05:32.970
Right!

91
00:05:34.310 --> 00:05:38.180
They got the set point first!

92
00:05:39.400 --> 00:05:40.980
Is something wrong?

93
00:05:40.980 --> 00:05:44.780
I was just thinking that Kei 
was acting a little weird.

94
00:05:45.410 --> 00:05:46.830
I might just be imagining it.

95
00:05:46.830 --> 00:05:50.170
His eyes seem much more lively than usual.

96
00:05:51.220 --> 00:05:55.350
Does Kei actually have friends
 at school besides Tadashi?

97
00:06:00.530 --> 00:06:01.340
Out?

98
00:06:01.340 --> 00:06:01.960
No...

99
00:06:03.550 --> 00:06:04.140
Cover!

100
00:06:04.140 --> 00:06:04.800
Left!

101
00:06:04.800 --> 00:06:05.560
Tanaka-san!

102
00:06:05.920 --> 00:06:07.420
Three blockers!

103
00:06:14.560 --> 00:06:15.820
A block out!

104
00:06:15.820 --> 00:06:16.860
Nice!

105
00:06:17.640 --> 00:06:19.770
Nice, Ryu!

106
00:06:18.930 --> 00:06:20.890
And now, it's a deuce.

107
00:06:19.770 --> 00:06:22.480
Karasuno                 Shiratorizawa

108
00:06:22.870 --> 00:06:24.350
All right!

109
00:06:24.350 --> 00:06:25.690
We're counting on you, Hinata!

110
00:06:26.230 --> 00:06:28.810
Make sure you get them back 
for all the times you got hit!

111
00:06:33.860 --> 00:06:34.740
Hey.

112
00:06:35.660 --> 00:06:39.280
Now Suga-chan can't come in 
anymore this time, right?

113
00:06:39.280 --> 00:06:40.380
Yeah.

114
00:06:40.380 --> 00:06:44.380
There's a rule where the same player can't 
be switched twice within the same set.

115
00:06:44.720 --> 00:06:47.460
But we got through Ushiwaka's serve.

116
00:06:47.460 --> 00:06:51.160
Now we amp up our attack power 
with Hinata on the front line.

117
00:06:51.160 --> 00:06:52.960
Karasuno definitely has the upper hand.

118
00:06:53.860 --> 00:06:55.640
Tsukishima, nice serve!

119
00:07:02.930 --> 00:07:04.820
One touch!

120
00:07:05.360 --> 00:07:06.020
Hey.

121
00:07:07.200 --> 00:07:10.260
If my serve is cleanly received,

122
00:07:10.690 --> 00:07:13.570
there's a good chance of them doing a quick.

123
00:07:14.610 --> 00:07:16.550
Try jumping as high as 
you can against their #5.

124
00:07:17.660 --> 00:07:18.440
Chance ball!

125
00:07:19.640 --> 00:07:22.470
Bring it!

126
00:07:21.000 --> 00:07:22.470
Give it to me!

127
00:07:26.390 --> 00:07:28.140
All right!

128
00:07:31.400 --> 00:07:32.790
A return dump...

129
00:07:34.280 --> 00:07:37.100
Man, people who hate to lose can be scary.

130
00:07:37.100 --> 00:07:38.670
It's not good for my heart.

131
00:07:38.670 --> 00:07:40.480
Nice, Kageyama!

132
00:07:41.960 --> 00:07:45.190
Yeah, great job, King.

133
00:07:45.190 --> 00:07:50.400
Tsukishima!

134
00:07:50.400 --> 00:07:53.070
Karasuno                 Shiratorizawa

135
00:07:50.980 --> 00:07:53.070
All right! They got it back!

136
00:07:53.330 --> 00:07:55.530
Now it's set point!

137
00:07:55.530 --> 00:07:58.240
Karasuno, fight!

138
00:08:02.290 --> 00:08:04.630
I'm sure this is extremely obvious,

139
00:08:05.280 --> 00:08:07.820
but it truly is hard to score

140
00:08:07.820 --> 00:08:09.440
more than one point in a row.

141
00:08:09.440 --> 00:08:10.840
Well, this game was designed

142
00:08:10.840 --> 00:08:13.500
so that each side has equal 
chances to attack.

143
00:08:13.500 --> 00:08:16.560
Not to mention, when we get 
into the last part of the set,

144
00:08:16.560 --> 00:08:18.870
each side gets that much more eager to win.

145
00:08:19.480 --> 00:08:20.480
But...

146
00:08:20.480 --> 00:08:22.480
Each side has to start scraping away

147
00:08:22.480 --> 00:08:24.100
at their opponent's sharpened defense.

148
00:08:25.030 --> 00:08:27.520
Even with pure height and power,

149
00:08:27.520 --> 00:08:29.480
their persistence, 
their ability to connect,

150
00:08:29.480 --> 00:08:33.500
and, to some extent, the calmness and 
stamina to maintain teamwork...

151
00:08:35.080 --> 00:08:37.930
In order to win, they need the 
tremendous amount of energy

152
00:08:37.930 --> 00:08:39.990
required to score two points in a row.

153
00:08:45.810 --> 00:08:49.430
They're still serving strong
like it's natural for them.

154
00:08:49.430 --> 00:08:50.590
That's to be expected from them.

155
00:08:50.590 --> 00:08:51.980
Sorry, it's long!

156
00:08:51.980 --> 00:08:53.550
Kageyama, push it over!

157
00:09:00.390 --> 00:09:01.500
Got it!

158
00:09:01.500 --> 00:09:02.430
Nice, Tsutomu!

159
00:09:02.840 --> 00:09:04.120
Chance ball!

160
00:09:10.640 --> 00:09:11.690
He's...

161
00:09:11.690 --> 00:09:13.150
Is he going to feint?

162
00:09:17.920 --> 00:09:19.240
He's going over there?

163
00:09:20.150 --> 00:09:21.240
There's...

164
00:09:21.510 --> 00:09:23.140
1.5 blockers!

165
00:09:25.340 --> 00:09:27.170
All right!

166
00:09:27.650 --> 00:09:31.020
He sure is a first-class decoy,  it...

167
00:09:28.150 --> 00:09:31.020
All right!

168
00:09:29.250 --> 00:09:30.840
Tanaka, nice kill!

169
00:09:32.120 --> 00:09:35.310
Did he set to their #5 because he knew

170
00:09:35.310 --> 00:09:36.810
our eyes would be on their #10?

171
00:09:37.670 --> 00:09:39.150
Nice toss, Kageyama!

172
00:09:39.150 --> 00:09:42.250
Actually, it was a little 
early... I'm sorry.

173
00:09:42.250 --> 00:09:44.100
You sure are hard on yourself.

174
00:09:44.560 --> 00:09:47.360
It really does piss people off when Hinata is

175
00:09:47.360 --> 00:09:49.160
scuttling around in front of you.

176
00:09:51.080 --> 00:09:52.980
Get as wild as you can,

177
00:09:54.230 --> 00:09:55.620
you weirdo duo.

178
00:09:56.930 --> 00:09:58.630
You fools!

179
00:09:56.930 --> 00:09:58.630
Karasuno              Shiratorizawa

180
00:10:02.660 --> 00:10:06.090
Shiratorizawa's taking their first time out!

181
00:10:07.040 --> 00:10:14.000
Haikyu!!
Karasuno High School vs Shiratorizawa Academy

182
00:10:14.090 --> 00:10:21.010
Haikyu!!
Karasuno High School vs Shiratorizawa Academy

183
00:10:22.720 --> 00:10:25.000
Shiratorizawa!

184
00:10:25.900 --> 00:10:28.330
Shiratorizawa!

185
00:10:28.770 --> 00:10:32.480
Karasuno              Shiratorizawa

186
00:10:29.880 --> 00:10:32.480
It's true that they're different 
from anyone we've faced so far.

187
00:10:32.850 --> 00:10:35.100
Shiratorizawa!

188
00:10:32.850 --> 00:10:35.710
But there's no reason for us to panic.

189
00:10:35.710 --> 00:10:39.450
We just have to score 
points like we usually do.

190
00:10:36.400 --> 00:10:38.500
Shiratorizawa!

191
00:10:39.790 --> 00:10:42.090
Shiratorizawa!

192
00:10:39.810 --> 00:10:41.310
Anyway, make sure to break their streak!

193
00:10:41.310 --> 00:10:42.180
Right!

194
00:10:43.210 --> 00:10:45.140
Shiratorizawa!

195
00:10:45.140 --> 00:10:47.260
Man... When I saw the first set,

196
00:10:47.260 --> 00:10:50.380
I thought it'd be an easy win 
for Shiratorizawa, but...

197
00:10:50.380 --> 00:10:52.010
I guess they're what you call a dark horse?

198
00:10:52.010 --> 00:10:55.250
But Karasuno's a former 
powerhouse school, too.

199
00:10:55.590 --> 00:10:58.220
Well, yeah. They've got 
Nishinoya from Chidoriyama,

200
00:10:58.220 --> 00:11:01.320
Kageyama from Kita-Ichi, 
and Azumane from Seikodai.

201
00:11:01.320 --> 00:11:03.020
They've got quite the lineup.

202
00:11:04.640 --> 00:11:07.120
Even if it gets rough, 
or you start panicking,

203
00:11:07.120 --> 00:11:08.630
don't let your guard down!

204
00:11:10.800 --> 00:11:12.300
All right!

205
00:11:13.360 --> 00:11:15.800
They can't seem to get 
those last two points...

206
00:11:15.800 --> 00:11:18.610
I'm pretty sure both sides are thinking that.

207
00:11:19.090 --> 00:11:22.320
However, if Karasuno loses this set,

208
00:11:22.320 --> 00:11:24.050
they're gonna be done.

209
00:11:24.050 --> 00:11:25.120
We're counting on you...

210
00:11:26.560 --> 00:11:29.080
We're counting on you, Eita-kun.

211
00:11:29.080 --> 00:11:29.930
Right!

212
00:11:31.000 --> 00:11:32.300
Semi-san!

213
00:11:32.300 --> 00:11:34.540
Semi! Get a nice serve in!

214
00:11:35.040 --> 00:11:38.000
So Shiratorizawa is using their pinch server.

215
00:11:38.420 --> 00:11:39.910
Nice serve, Eita!

216
00:11:47.330 --> 00:11:48.190
Sorry!

217
00:11:48.640 --> 00:11:49.520
Daichi-san!

218
00:11:51.480 --> 00:11:52.800
Above you, Shirabu!

219
00:11:52.800 --> 00:11:53.540
Right!

220
00:11:55.120 --> 00:11:55.900
Semi-san!

221
00:11:57.090 --> 00:11:58.280
Come on, Tsutomu!

222
00:11:58.640 --> 00:11:59.280
Right!

223
00:12:03.950 --> 00:12:06.010
All right!

224
00:12:06.640 --> 00:12:08.870
Break!

225
00:12:06.960 --> 00:12:08.390
Yeah!

226
00:12:08.410 --> 00:12:11.400
Nice kill, Goshiki!

227
00:12:08.870 --> 00:12:12.290
Karasuno             Shiratorizawa

228
00:12:12.590 --> 00:12:14.630
Come to think of it, I guess he was a setter.

229
00:12:16.770 --> 00:12:18.540
Concentrate!

230
00:12:18.540 --> 00:12:19.760
Right!

231
00:12:20.310 --> 00:12:21.470
Nice serve!

232
00:12:23.970 --> 00:12:24.800
Daichi!

233
00:12:25.400 --> 00:12:26.760
! It's short!

234
00:12:27.070 --> 00:12:28.180
All right. It's off.

235
00:12:32.220 --> 00:12:33.240
Huh?!

236
00:12:33.940 --> 00:12:35.910
All right!

237
00:12:36.570 --> 00:12:40.030
A quick there?! You guys 
are seriously messed up!

238
00:12:40.280 --> 00:12:42.470
Hinata, nice kill!

239
00:12:42.470 --> 00:12:46.700
Looks like logic doesn't 
work on this side either.

240
00:12:49.650 --> 00:12:52.660
Who does Karasuno's setter think he is?

241
00:12:52.660 --> 00:12:54.870
Karasuno              Shiratorizawa

242
00:12:53.380 --> 00:12:55.620
Tanaka, nice serve!

243
00:12:58.130 --> 00:12:58.910
Got it!

244
00:12:58.910 --> 00:13:01.340
Come on, break... Break through!

245
00:12:59.830 --> 00:13:00.920
Left!

246
00:13:07.310 --> 00:13:08.220
All right!

247
00:13:08.870 --> 00:13:10.140
Wakatoshi!

248
00:13:10.580 --> 00:13:11.780
Three blockers!

249
00:13:14.170 --> 00:13:18.360
! It looks like that libero's 
getting the hang of it.

250
00:13:18.360 --> 00:13:21.600
But Ushiwaka's still only using 
about 70% of his strength.

251
00:13:21.600 --> 00:13:23.280
Would you be able to get those?

252
00:13:23.280 --> 00:13:24.320
Not a chance.

253
00:13:30.000 --> 00:13:30.540
!

254
00:13:30.000 --> 00:13:31.660
All right!

255
00:13:30.540 --> 00:13:32.160
Sorry! It was close to the net!

256
00:13:32.160 --> 00:13:35.120
Karasuno              Shiratorizawa

257
00:13:36.380 --> 00:13:38.620
We're not done yet... We've only just begun!

258
00:13:39.540 --> 00:13:41.250
Shirabu-san, nice serve!

259
00:13:41.880 --> 00:13:42.840
Got it!

260
00:13:43.510 --> 00:13:44.780
Nice receive!

261
00:13:44.780 --> 00:13:45.670
Right!

262
00:13:49.110 --> 00:13:50.750
All right!

263
00:13:49.670 --> 00:13:50.750
!

264
00:13:50.750 --> 00:13:52.060
Nice, Daichi!

265
00:13:50.750 --> 00:13:52.060
Yes!

266
00:13:56.240 --> 00:13:58.700
There's no way that I can beat Ushiwaka.

267
00:14:02.620 --> 00:14:05.920
Our bodies are different. 
Our experience is different.

268
00:14:05.920 --> 00:14:08.450
The time we've given volleyball is different.

269
00:14:09.520 --> 00:14:11.160
There's no way that I can beat him.

270
00:14:16.000 --> 00:14:16.840
But...

271
00:14:24.570 --> 00:14:26.540
I was hoping they could break through

272
00:14:26.540 --> 00:14:28.880
while they still had Hinata as a decoy.

273
00:14:28.880 --> 00:14:31.800
Hinata looks so anxious 
on the back line.

274
00:14:32.210 --> 00:14:35.500
He sucks at both serving and digs...

275
00:14:41.650 --> 00:14:43.100
Hinata, nice serve!

276
00:14:43.100 --> 00:14:43.820
Right!

277
00:14:44.720 --> 00:14:46.820
If their #5's guess blocking

278
00:14:47.500 --> 00:14:49.860
is either 120 points or 0 points,

279
00:14:50.820 --> 00:14:55.110
I'd say read blocking stays at 
about an average of 75 points.

280
00:14:58.060 --> 00:15:01.580
Well, our blocks definitely need more work,

281
00:15:01.920 --> 00:15:05.550
but maybe it looks cooler to bystanders

282
00:15:02.360 --> 00:15:03.530
Nice serve!

283
00:15:05.550 --> 00:15:07.010
when people go for the 120 points.

284
00:15:09.800 --> 00:15:14.570
We can't let the opponent setter 
feel the pleasure or accomplishment

285
00:15:14.570 --> 00:15:16.430
of overcoming our blocks.

286
00:15:16.680 --> 00:15:17.280
Got it!

287
00:15:17.280 --> 00:15:20.350
Persistently, begrudgingly,

288
00:15:18.640 --> 00:15:19.640
Nice receive!

289
00:15:20.760 --> 00:15:23.660
yet nimbly, and absolutely...

290
00:15:26.980 --> 00:15:28.820
They won't get through easily.

291
00:15:30.310 --> 00:15:34.450
Continue pressuring them 
and piling on stress.

292
00:15:35.000 --> 00:15:36.160
One touch!

293
00:15:41.790 --> 00:15:43.640
Connect!

294
00:15:46.060 --> 00:15:47.270
Hit! Hit!

295
00:15:50.840 --> 00:15:52.040
Nice, Tachi!

296
00:15:51.060 --> 00:15:52.040
Got it!

297
00:15:53.680 --> 00:15:56.240
You suck at serving, you suck at receiving,

298
00:15:56.240 --> 00:15:59.430
and your setting and
 blocking are below average.

299
00:15:59.430 --> 00:16:01.390
Then what are you doing on the court?

300
00:16:03.500 --> 00:16:05.060
You score points!

301
00:16:10.490 --> 00:16:11.770
All right!

302
00:16:10.490 --> 00:16:12.950
Karasuno                Shiratorizawa

303
00:16:11.770 --> 00:16:12.950
Break!

304
00:16:13.670 --> 00:16:15.690
A back attack with minus tempo.

305
00:16:13.670 --> 00:16:15.690
Great job, Hinata!

306
00:16:15.690 --> 00:16:18.660
He's gotten even faster after 
that time Oikawa stopped him.

307
00:16:18.660 --> 00:16:21.850
Taichi! Don't just stand there!

308
00:16:21.850 --> 00:16:23.870
Nah, that one was impossible.

309
00:16:24.180 --> 00:16:25.240
Nice one touch!

310
00:16:24.550 --> 00:16:26.330
Hinata, one more! Nice serve!

311
00:16:26.330 --> 00:16:28.360
If it weren't for Hinata's cover,

312
00:16:28.360 --> 00:16:30.590
it would have just been blown away.

313
00:16:30.590 --> 00:16:32.680
But if we didn't have that one touch,

314
00:16:32.680 --> 00:16:35.300
we might have been done right then.

315
00:16:38.290 --> 00:16:39.220
Shirabu.

316
00:16:41.520 --> 00:16:42.820
Gather them to me.

317
00:16:47.120 --> 00:16:48.490
Crap!

318
00:16:49.810 --> 00:16:54.070
Out? But if I judge wrong 
here, I'm going to be killed!

319
00:16:55.880 --> 00:16:56.950
It went in!

320
00:16:55.880 --> 00:16:56.950
It's off.

321
00:16:57.200 --> 00:16:58.110
I'm sorry!

322
00:16:58.110 --> 00:16:58.910
Wakatoshi!

323
00:16:59.480 --> 00:17:00.960
We've got three.

324
00:17:00.960 --> 00:17:03.160
Ready, and...

325
00:17:07.380 --> 00:17:11.060
Nice kill, Ushijima!

326
00:17:11.840 --> 00:17:13.190
Ushijima!

327
00:17:13.560 --> 00:17:15.000
Ushijima!

328
00:17:16.260 --> 00:17:18.220
Karasuno              Shiratorizawa

329
00:17:19.160 --> 00:17:21.280
That was intense...

330
00:17:21.280 --> 00:17:25.100
It was like he changed the flow of 
the game with a single strike.

331
00:17:25.640 --> 00:17:28.360
Don't fall behind! We're 
going to keep going forward!

332
00:17:28.360 --> 00:17:29.110
Right!

333
00:17:37.280 --> 00:17:38.320
That was intense.

334
00:17:43.600 --> 00:17:44.370
All right!

335
00:17:45.330 --> 00:17:47.190
Synchronized attack!

336
00:17:51.720 --> 00:17:55.420
We're definitely not losing
 when it comes to scoring points.

337
00:17:54.400 --> 00:17:56.510
Yeah!

338
00:17:58.970 --> 00:18:01.180
Karasuno              Shiratorizawa

339
00:18:02.390 --> 00:18:04.140
Daichi-san, nice serve!

340
00:18:08.020 --> 00:18:08.810
Ushijima-san!

341
00:18:10.730 --> 00:18:12.270
Ready, and...

342
00:18:16.460 --> 00:18:17.900
So persistent!

343
00:18:18.920 --> 00:18:20.040
Return it! Return it!

344
00:18:20.720 --> 00:18:21.620
Nice, Daichi-san!

345
00:18:22.370 --> 00:18:23.560
Chance ball!

346
00:18:30.920 --> 00:18:33.380
Open the way...

347
00:18:33.660 --> 00:18:35.220
for our spiker!

348
00:18:38.260 --> 00:18:40.050
I was waiting

349
00:18:40.050 --> 00:18:42.790
for this fraying caused

350
00:18:44.070 --> 00:18:45.380
by slight annoyance and panic.

351
00:19:19.910 --> 00:19:22.470
There's no way that I can beat Ushiwaka.

352
00:19:23.350 --> 00:19:24.220
But...

353
00:19:27.350 --> 00:19:30.010
I'm planning on stopping at 
least a few of his spikes.

354
00:19:30.920 --> 00:19:32.560
He stopped Ushiwaka?!

355
00:19:32.560 --> 00:19:33.840
Who is that guy?

356
00:19:33.840 --> 00:19:34.610
No idea!

357
00:19:34.610 --> 00:19:35.960
Amazing!

358
00:19:34.610 --> 00:19:37.570
Karasuno              Shiratorizawa

359
00:19:35.960 --> 00:19:39.400
They took back the second set!

360
00:19:42.320 --> 00:19:44.150
It was just one block.

361
00:19:44.690 --> 00:19:47.290
It was just one point out of 25.

362
00:19:48.130 --> 00:19:50.760
This is just a club.

363
00:19:52.770 --> 00:19:54.960
But once that moment arrives for you,

364
00:19:56.500 --> 00:20:00.870
that's the moment you'll 
be hooked on volleyball.

365
00:19:59.710 --> 00:20:03.260
All right!

366
00:20:12.600 --> 00:20:15.900
Tsukishima!

367
00:20:15.900 --> 00:20:16.860
Ow!

368
00:20:16.860 --> 00:20:19.090
Ushiwaka's spike just now...

369
00:20:17.850 --> 00:20:21.350
Tsukshima, are you seriously Tsukishima? 
Did you seriously just seriously?

370
00:20:19.090 --> 00:20:21.370
There wasn't a moment to spare 
in his run or his jump.

371
00:20:21.940 --> 00:20:26.740
But the toss was probably a bit 
close to the net and low...

372
00:20:27.410 --> 00:20:29.720
Tsukishima didn't let that escape him.

373
00:20:30.840 --> 00:20:31.690
Or...

374
00:20:32.210 --> 00:20:33.420
Was he waiting for that?

375
00:20:35.120 --> 00:20:37.980
Sorry for saying something 
like we could still fight,

376
00:20:37.980 --> 00:20:39.820
even if we can't stop him with our blocks.

377
00:20:39.820 --> 00:20:40.500
Huh?

378
00:20:40.920 --> 00:20:44.470
You were making a weird 
face back then, Yamaguchi.

379
00:20:44.470 --> 00:20:45.240
Huh?!

380
00:20:45.240 --> 00:20:49.720
No, I was also thinking that Tsukki 
was definitely doing his part.

381
00:20:50.640 --> 00:20:54.000
Despite how he looks, 
Tsukki hates losing,

382
00:20:54.000 --> 00:20:56.700
so I figured he would probably do something.

383
00:20:57.480 --> 00:20:59.440
Tsukishima, nice block!

384
00:20:59.440 --> 00:21:00.840
Great job stopping that!

385
00:21:01.240 --> 00:21:04.780
I'm sure there were other blockers 
before that were at my level,

386
00:21:05.150 --> 00:21:08.250
but I think that Nishinoya-san's receives

387
00:21:08.250 --> 00:21:10.580
and that weirdo duo's attack 
that completely ignores their blocks

388
00:21:11.060 --> 00:21:13.790
added pressure to their setter.

389
00:21:16.370 --> 00:21:18.960
You were thinking about all that?

390
00:21:18.960 --> 00:21:21.130
Scary... Tsukishima, you're scary.

391
00:21:22.160 --> 00:21:25.960
I think that Kei might have been 
waiting this whole time for the timing

392
00:21:25.960 --> 00:21:27.960
of Shiratorizawa's tosses to skew.

393
00:21:29.170 --> 00:21:31.850
I can't believe he thought that far ahead.

394
00:21:32.390 --> 00:21:34.890
Tsukishima-kun is smart,

395
00:21:35.310 --> 00:21:37.480
so I believe that he's always

396
00:21:37.480 --> 00:21:40.990
thinking about volleyball, 
as well as other things...

397
00:21:40.990 --> 00:21:43.560
I'm sure he's pretty obstinate.
Sorry about that.

398
00:21:43.560 --> 00:21:45.050
Oh, no...

399
00:21:45.750 --> 00:21:48.270
It's just that at that moment,

400
00:21:48.270 --> 00:21:52.790
I think the only thing on Tsukishima-kun's 
mind was stopping that block.

401
00:21:53.650 --> 00:21:55.150
Just purely...

402
00:21:56.230 --> 00:21:58.790
Like he was solving a 
difficult test question.

403
00:22:01.160 --> 00:22:01.880
Yeah.

404
00:22:03.190 --> 00:22:04.310
Tsukishima!

405
00:22:07.090 --> 00:22:09.840
That one point was worth 100 points!

406
00:22:13.850 --> 00:22:17.640
If you're a
middle blocker,

407
00:22:13.850 --> 00:22:17.640
you try it, too

408
00:22:14.690 --> 00:22:15.690
Thanks.

409
00:22:19.080 --> 00:22:21.040
What?!

410
00:22:21.040 --> 00:22:22.350
Calm down, Hinata!

411
00:22:22.350 --> 00:22:25.790
I'm sure he meant it as,
 "If you're a middle blocker, you try it, too,"

412
00:22:25.790 --> 00:22:26.900
but calm down!

413
00:22:27.540 --> 00:22:29.850
Please stop making such a fuss.

414
00:22:32.660 --> 00:22:33.900
That was just a point.

415
00:22:34.760 --> 00:22:37.480
The game's just getting starting.

416
00:22:38.140 --> 00:22:39.860
Yeah!

417
00:24:12.660 --> 00:24:14.890
Tsukki finally stopped Ushiwaka!

418
00:24:14.890 --> 00:24:17.790
Kei usually doesn't show 
his emotions and is blunt,

419
00:24:17.790 --> 00:24:21.180
but he actually works really hard, 
is kind, and is a really good boy.

420
00:24:21.560 --> 00:24:23.060
Who are you, his mother?!

421
00:24:23.060 --> 00:24:26.170
Next time on Haikyu!!: 
"Individual VS Numbers."

422
00:24:24.100 --> 00:24:27.020
Episode 05: Individual VS Numbers
